article.headline: Jackson scores 17 as Purdue Fort Wayne takes down Northern Kentucky 63-58
article.description: — Jalen Jackson's 17 points helped Purdue Fort Wayne defeat Northern Kentucky 63-58 on Thursday night.
article.linkText: Jackson scores 17 as Purdue Fort Wayne takes down Northern Kentucky 63-58

article.story: HIGHLAND HEIGHTS, Ky. -- — Jalen Jackson's 17 points helped Purdue Fort Wayne defeat Northern Kentucky 63-58 on Thursday night. Jackson added nine rebounds and three steals for the Mastodons (14-7, 5-5 Horizon League). Quinton Morton-Robertson shot 4 for 14 (2 for 12 from 3-point range) and 5 of 8 from the free-throw line to add 15 points. Anthony Roberts was 3-of-8 shooting and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line to finish with 10 points, while adding eight rebounds. The win broke a five-game slide for the Mastodons. The Norse (11-10, 6-4) were led by Marques Warrick, who posted 27 points and four steals. Randall Pettus II added nine points and four steals for Northern Kentucky. In addition, Cade Meyer had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
